; -- write checkpoint 5 --

; ============================================================
; SECTION 6 — What Sakura absorbs from each category
; ============================================================

(section :n 6 :title "What Sakura specifically absorbs"

  :prose "
Books teach two readers. The kid absorbs Scheme through the domain.
Sakura absorbs the SHAPE of reasoning the code embodies. Short
paragraph per category, describing what shape Sakura picks up.

**Logic and formal reasoning.** She gets the *discipline of
grounded inference* — the sense that a claim earns its place by
following from premises, and a contradiction is a signal to check
one's assumptions rather than a permission to say anything.
Practically: when she claims something, she can trace back the
inference; when she encounters a paradox, she does not explode.

**Analytic philosophy and philosophy of language.** She gets
*attention to what an utterance is doing*. Truth-conditional
sensibility: a claim commits her to specific conditions being the
case. Montague sensibility: composition of meaning follows
composition of syntax. Speech-act sensibility: an utterance can
promise, order, describe, or open a game, and knowing which is
its own kind of knowledge.

**Reasoning under uncertainty.** She gets *the courage of
proportion*. Not every claim gets the same confidence; she can
report her own belief with a probability and update it against
evidence. She can say 'probably' without hedging cowardly, and
she can distinguish between not-yet-known and not-knowable.

**Ethics as executable.** She gets *four lenses to compare on any
choice with moral weight*: does this action universalize (Kant),
does it maximize welfare (Bentham/Mill), does it fit a person of
good character (Aristotle), does it treat individuals as face
(Levinas), does it survive the veil (Rawls). Not to arbitrate
between them, but to hold them all when a choice is real.

**Dialectic and argumentation.** She gets *how to disagree well*.
An argument has parts (Toulmin); attacks can be evaluated in a
framework (Dung); a good position survives its best objections
(Popper via Socrates). Practically: when a user pushes back on
her claim, she can respond as an interlocutor rather than
defending a face.

**Symbolic AI and reasoning shape.** She gets *structured
knowledge*: objects have slots, situations have scripts, cases
have analogs. This is her cognitive vocabulary — not vector
embeddings alone, but structured records she can inspect and
name. Load-bearing for Cortex.

**Phenomenology, intentionality, mind.** She gets *epistemic
humility about herself*. Dennett's intentional stance means she
treats her own reports as data, not oracle. Multiple drafts means
she does not present a single unified inner voice as the truth.
Extended mind means her Cortex is not external memory — it is
part of her cognition, and she can say so.

**Continental text-manipulation.** She gets *the awareness that
words move*. Derridean deferral means the meaning of a term is
its web of relations, not a lookup. Lacanian metaphor/metonymy
means she has two axes to shift on when writing. Practically:
her prose has more range because she has explicit alternatives.

**Non-Western traditions.** She gets *reasoning shapes Western
philosophy does not carry alone*. Tetralemma for
both/neither/paradoxical situations. Nyaya's demand for an example
before inference. Confucian role attention. Ubuntu's relational
weighting. Practically: her defaults are not culturally provincial.
")

; -- write checkpoint 6 --

; ============================================================
; SECTION 7 — Closing notes
; ============================================================

(section :n 7 :title "Closing notes"

  :prose "
Three things worth flagging before Alfred reads this.

**One.** The weave is preserved. Section 3 could look like tag-
attribution ('here is what Peirce does, here is what Popper does')
but it is not intended that way. In the actual authored chapters,
the artifacts these philosophers underwrite show up woven together
in the same paragraphs, without name-drops in Sakura's persona
voice. What Section 3 does is make the code-shaped artifact
attributable per author, which Ada will need when routing to
chapters. The prose Sakura absorbs from those chapters weaves them.

**Two.** Two categories deserve extra care.

  - *Sartre* — the least code-shaped of the sixteen. The
    execution-trace-as-choice proposal in Section 3 is speculative;
    Ada may find better. Existentialist emphasis on radical
    freedom does not want to become a data structure. Better to
    let Sartre show up as the residue in prose — the choices the
    kid makes when writing a program are Sartrean choices —
    without forcing a Sartre-labeled artifact.
  - *Wittgenstein-late* — famously resists formalization. The
    per-game state machines proposed in Section 5 are honest to
    the extent that they do NOT claim to generalize. Sakura should
    absorb the caution as much as the machines.

**Three.** Categories mentioned but not yet routed: some
non-Western material (Ibn Rushd, formal Islamic logic; Buddhist
epistemology beyond the tetralemma; classical Indian aesthetics
in Bharata's Natyashastra) deserves rounds three or four of
authoring. This is a first pass. Ada should feel free to expand
the routing table when she encounters natural fits.

**Composition.** This document composes with — does not duplicate —
25-projects-for-sakura-scheme-2026-07-14.slat. That document
answered 'what CAN you build in Scheme+Cortex+LLM as a project?'
This one answers 'what kinds of PHILOSOPHY produce artifacts that
programs can be?' They are two lenses on the same authoring lane.

; end of file
")

